Diagnosis.
Vertex weakly carinate behind ocellar triangle (Fig. 4). Petiole 1.45x longer than broad in females (Fig. 6), 1.67x in males, its apex not reaching metacoxal apex in females. First funicular segment 2.33x longer than broad (
Fig. 1
). Scape at rest not extending above median ocellus (
Fig. 1
).

Petiole 0.8x0.55 (Fig. 6), gaster 4.5x2.3, ovate (
Fig. 1
). Petiole parallel­sided, falling distinctly short of metacoxal apex. Gastral base with a very weak dorso­lateral carina on each side of the petiolar base, bordered medially by a narrow fovea, these extending for 0.3 from petiolar base. First gastral tergite 0.2x gastral length, truncate posteriorly. Hypopygium reaching 0.8x gastral length, with a deep apical vase­shaped incision with rounded contours. Cercus with 1 seta distinctly longer than the others, with a sharp apical curve.
